  <steps>
    <step order="1">Invoke `/code-review` on the project — identify remaining issues; fix critical ones in a follow-up commit.</step>
    <step order="2">Invoke `/adr-check` — validate ADR compliance across all changed code; fix any violations.</step>
    <step order="3">Invoke `/repo-cleanup projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r2` — audit + clean ephemeral files; archive `notes/handoffs/` to `.archive/`.</step>
    <step order="4">Update README: Status → Complete; Last Updated → today; Progress → 100%; Completed Date set; check off all 14 graduation criteria; add Changelog entry.</step>
    <step order="5">Update plan.md: Status → Complete; all milestones → ✅.</step>
    <step order="6">Author `notes/lessons-learned.md` covering:</step>
    <step order="7">  • R1 retrospective (gap fill — what R1 producer-layer shipped, why it was solid, missing pieces consumer-side that R2 had to fix)</step>
    <step order="8">  • R2 learnings (Pattern D dual-use migration pattern; effect-based hook coordination; AI-output validation as defense in depth; toasttype-conditional `data.actions[]`)</step>
    <step order="9">  • Anti-patterns avoided (didn't extend `@spaarke/ui-components`; didn't keep monolithic `useNotificationData`)</step>
    <step order="10">  • Surprises/gotchas (anything unexpected during implementation)</step>
    <step order="11">Verify all task files marked ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md.</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 090 status from 🔲 to ✅.</step>
  </steps>

